fb32e781-fe5f-4a50-a678-6730ffa8ea9f.243e4c9e-00ad-4088-9032-3530c2fc4cdc.description=
Runs the requested SQL Command, returns the number of row(s) affected and any lateral effect.

Inputs\:
host	- Hostname or IP address of the SQL Server.
username	- The username of the SQL or Windows user credentials to login to the SQL Server.  If use Windows authentication, username input should be in the format like\: domain\username. 
password	- Password of the user account.
instance        - The named instance of SQL Server. Leave it blank for default instance.
dbPort	- The port on which the SQL Server database service is listening on.
database 	- The name of the database to run the command on.
authType	- Whether Windows authentication or SQL authentication should be used. Default is SQL.
command 	- The actual SQL command to run (either T-SQL, Stored Procedure, or Extended procedure).
timeout 	- Seconds to wait before timing out the SQL command execution. It defaults to 30 seconds.

Result\:
The number of rows affected.

Extra results\:
outputText -	 Output result for the command (if this is the case).

Responses\:
success 	- The command was successful.
failure 	- There was a problem running the command.

Notes\:
1. When informational commands (like dbcc) are run through the command, end the command with "with tableresults" in order to populate the outputText output with the obtained result.
2. Use the Sql Query operation instead of Sql Command when Select queries are to be run.
3. Please refer to the Notes in the Microsoft SQL folder description for the general integration information of Microsoft SQL Server.
fb32e781-fe5f-4a50-a678-6730ffa8ea9f.64db1f81-e128-49a3-bee5-7dd67af44448.transition.description=Rework fb32e781-fe5f-4a50-a678-6730ffa8ea9f.653db309-4b40-4c5a-9303-01114684b5e4.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex (The values are not case sensitive)
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

fb32e781-fe5f-4a50-a678-6730ffa8ea9f.df9bdc0f-bd19-4bbd-a3d6-724919891576.transition.description=Failure fb32e781-fe5f-4a50-a678-6730ffa8ea9f.e304469d-97ad-4675-9c42-11666683e166.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
    string1 - The first string. 
Default value\: "" (empty)
    string2 - The second string.
Default value\: "" (empty)
    ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

Responses\:
    true - If the two strings are equal.
    false - If the two strings are not equal.
